A machine learning framework for detecting and classifying gold mineralization levels from geochemical datasets. The project evaluates tree-based ensemble models under class imbalance and emphasizes recall-driven, decision-supportoriented evaluation rather than accuracy-only prediction.

The project applies traditional machine-learning techniques and contextual feature engineering to estimate expected passing yards and evaluate sportsbook prop lines, with performance assessed using realistic historical backtesting.

ASEADOSSDNIoT, a novel and publicly available intrusion detection dataset supported by a fully documented hybrid testbed framework. The resulting dataset contains 457,044 labeled flow instances with 83 statistical features and was evaluated using state-of-the-art machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques.

This project analyzes time-varying volatility in financial markets using a GARCH(1,1) framework and compares it with machine-learningbased volatility estimation. The study focuses on volatility clustering, regime behavior, and model robustness across calm and stress periods rather than return prediction.

A simple rule-based AI chatbot built using pure Python (Python 3.14.2 compatible) without any external libraries or machine learning frameworks. The chatbot uses pattern matching and decision rules to simulate intelligent conversation, making it ideal for learning the fundamentals of Artificial Intelligence, NLP basics, and Python programming.

Intelligent Real Estate Agent is an AI-driven system designed to analyze real estate data, estimate property values, and assist users in making informed housing decisions. The project integrates data preprocessing, feature engineering, and machine learning techniques to build a robust predictive and analytical framework for the real estate market.

AI vs. Human Text Detection Framework A machine learning benchmarking system designed to distinguish between AI-generated and human-written text in Bengali and English. It utilizes novel graph-based feature extraction, rigorous statistical validation, and multi-model benchmarking against state-of-the-art baselines like DetectGPT and Grover.
